Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
deleteCellEdgeSpacing(25.10)                      deleteCellEdgeSpacing(25.10)

Name
       deleteCellEdgeSpacing

Syntax
       deleteCellEdgeSpacing

       [-help]

       <edgeType1>

       <edgeType2>

       Deletes  the spacing rule between two edge types. The edge types speci-
       fied must be predefined.

       Note: This command only deletes the cell edge constraint  specified  by
       Tcl and does not delete the edge spacing defined in LEF.

Parameters
       <edgeType1>
              Specifies edge type1 for edge spacing.

       <edgeType1>
              Specifies edge type2 for edge spacing.

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each deleteCellEdgeSpacing parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man deleteCellEdgeSpacing.

Related Information
              * report_cell_edge_spacing

              * specifyCellEdgeSpacing

